<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,439,645]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Although described as a separate genus, it was for long treated as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fitzinger" authorityYear="1843" box="[1117,1258,476,501]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Cyrtopodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1117,1258,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Cyrtopodion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bohme, W." box="[1278,1431,476,501]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="95 - 98" refId="ref47513" refString="Bohme, W. (1985) Zur Nomenklatur der palaarktischen Bogenfingergeckos, Gattung Tenuidactylus Scerbak &amp; Golubew, 1984. Bonner zoologische Beitrage, 36, 95 - 98." type="journal article" year="1985">Böhme 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Anderson, S. C." box="[151,326,511,536]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref45318" refString="Anderson, S. C. (1999) The lizards of Iran. Society for the Study of Amphibians and Reptiles, Oxford, Ohio, 442 pp." type="book" year="1999">Anderson 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sindaco, R. &amp; Jeremcenko, V. K." box="[337,665,511,536]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref65138" refString="Sindaco, R. &amp; Jeremcenko, V. K. (2008) The reptiles of the Western Palearctic. 1. Annotated checklist and distributional atlas of the turtles, crocodiles, amphisbaenians and lizards of Europe, North Africa, Middle East and Central Asia. Monografie della Societas Herpetologica Italica, Edizioni Belvedere, 579 pp." type="book" year="2008">Sindaco &amp; Jeremčenko 2008</bibRefCitation>
). Recent phylogenetic studies show the distinctness of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Szczerbak &amp; Golubev" authorityYear="1984" box="[1279,1436,511,536]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Tenuidactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1279,1436,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Tenuidactylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and prove its genus level is justified (
<bibRefCitation author="Gamble, T. &amp; Greenbaum, E. &amp; Jackman, T. R. &amp; Russell, A. P. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[579,803,548,573]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="39429" refId="ref51406" refString="Gamble, T., Greenbaum, E., Jackman, T. R., Russell, A. P. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2012) Repeated Origin and Loss of Adhesive Toepads in Geckos. PLoS ONE, 7, e 39429. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0039429" type="journal article" year="2012">
Gamble 
<emphasis box="[678,736,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bauer, A. M. &amp; Masroor, R. &amp; Titus-Mcquillan, J. &amp; Heinicke, M. P. &amp; Daza, J. D. &amp; Jackman, T. R." box="[817,1019,548,573]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="301 - 324" refId="ref46979" refString="Bauer, A. M., Masroor, R., Titus-Mcquillan, J., Heinicke, M. P., Daza, J. D. &amp; Jackman, T. R. (2013) A preliminary phylogeny of the Palearctic naked-toed geckos (Reptilia: Squamata: Gekkonidae) with taxonomic implications. Zootaxa, 3599 (4), 301 - 324. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3599.4.1" type="journal article" year="2013">
Bauer 
<emphasis box="[892,950,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). However, its phylogenetic position with respect to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fitzinger" authorityYear="1843" box="[330,471,583,608]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Cyrtopodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[330,471,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Cyrtopodion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not been satisfactorily resolved. 
<bibRefCitation author="Cervenka, J. &amp; Kratochvil, L. &amp; Frynta, D." box="[900,1158,583,608]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="25 - 36" refId="ref48285" refString="Cervenka, J., Kratochvil, L. &amp; Frynta, D. (2008) Phylogeny and taxonomy of the Middle Eastern geckos of the genus Cyrtopodion and their selected relatives. Zootaxa, 1931, 25 - 36." type="journal article" year="2008">
Červenka 
<emphasis box="[1016,1067,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al</emphasis>
. (2008)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Pyron, R. &amp; Burbrink, F. &amp; Wiens, J." box="[1217,1436,583,608]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="93" refId="ref62209" refString="Pyron, R., Burbrink, F. &amp; Wiens, J. (2013) A phylogeny and revised classification of Squamata, including 4161 species of lizards and snakes. BMC Evolutionary Biology, 13, 93. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1186 / 1471 - 2148 - 13 - 93" type="journal article" year="2013">
Pyron 
<emphasis box="[1293,1345,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al</emphasis>
. (2013)
</bibRefCitation>
placed it between the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Nikolsky" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[395,541,620,645]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Cyrtopodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="agamuroides">
<emphasis box="[395,541,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">agamuroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[596,692,620,645]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Cyrtopodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scabrum">
<emphasis box="[596,692,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">scabrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
groups of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fitzinger" authorityYear="1843" box="[812,953,620,645]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Cyrtopodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[812,953,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Cyrtopodion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, thus rendering 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fitzinger" authorityYear="1843" box="[1136,1277,620,645]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Cyrtopodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1136,1277,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Cyrtopodion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
paraphyletic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
